<div1 type="trialAccount" id="t17490705-14">
               <interp inst="t17490705-14" type="collection" value="BAILEY"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17490705-14" type="year" value="1749"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17490705-14" type="uri" value="sessionsPapers/17490705"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17490705-14" type="date" value="17490705"></interp>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t17490705-14-off73-c85" targOrder="Y" targets="t17490705-14-defend103 t17490705-14-off73 t17490705-14-verdict77"></join>
         
               <p>385. 
               <persName id="t17490705-14-defend103" type="defendantName">
                  James 
                  Hill 
               <interp inst="t17490705-14-defend103" type="surname" value="Hill"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17490705-14-defend103" type="given" value="James"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17490705-14-defend103" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , late of <placeName id="t17490705-14-defloc72">St. Martin's in the Fields</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17490705-14-defloc72" type="placeName" value="St. Martin's in the Fields"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17490705-14-defloc72" type="type" value="defendantHome"></interp>
                  <join result="persNamePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17490705-14-defend103 t17490705-14-defloc72"></join>, was indicted for a <rs id="t17490705-14-off73" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17490705-14-off73" type="offenceCategory" value="violentTheft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17490705-14-off73" type="offenceSubcategory" value="highwayRobbery"></interp>
               robbery on the King's high-way, on the person of 
                     
                        <persName id="t17490705-14-victim105" type="victimName">
                           Thomas 
                           Page 
                        <interp inst="t17490705-14-victim105" type="surname" value="Page"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17490705-14-victim105" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17490705-14-victim105" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t17490705-14-off73 t17490705-14-victim105"></join>
                     </persName>
                      
                  , putting him in corporal fear, &amp;c. and taking from him one periwig, val. 10 s. against the will of the said Thomas
            </rs>, <rs id="t17490705-14-cd74" type="crimeDate">May 16</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17490705-14-off73 t17490705-14-cd74"></join>
               </p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17490705-14-person106">
                  Thomas 
                  Page 
               <interp inst="t17490705-14-person106" type="surname" value="Page"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17490705-14-person106" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17490705-14-person106" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . As I was going along the <placeName id="t17490705-14-crimeloc75">Strand</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17490705-14-crimeloc75" type="placeName" value="Strand"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17490705-14-crimeloc75" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17490705-14-off73 t17490705-14-crimeloc75"></join>, near <placeName id="t17490705-14-crimeloc76">Round Court</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17490705-14-crimeloc76" type="placeName" value="Round Court"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17490705-14-crimeloc76" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17490705-14-off73 t17490705-14-crimeloc76"></join>, the 16th of May about eleven at night, I felt my periwig going from my head, upon which I clap'd my hand to my hat to save that, I turned and saw the prisoner at the bar, with my wig in his hand; he run, I pursued him, crying stop thief! he did not run above a hundred yards before he was stop'd; he was never out of me fight, and it was a very moon-light night; he ask'd me what he had done, I told him he had rob'd me of my periwig; he had drop'd it between his legs, and I took it up.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I happened to be coming by at that time, being a little way up the Court, I heard somebody cry, stop thief! I happen'd to light of the wig that lay there; there were two men laid hold of me, I knew nothing of the wig.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17490705-14-verdict77" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17490705-14-verdict77" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17490705-14-verdict77" type="verdictSubcategory" value="lesserOffence"></interp>
               Guilty of Felony only
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17490705-14-punish78" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17490705-14-punish78" type="punishmentCategory" value="transport"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t17490705-14-defend103 t17490705-14-punish78"></join>
               
                     <note>[Transportation. See summary.]</note>
               
                  </rs>
               </p>
            </div1>
